                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                            <locus from="77r" to="79v"/>
                            <title type="complete" ref="LIT7026PrayerGod"/>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            <note><bibl><ptr target="bm:Loefgren1974Katalog"/><citedRange unit="page">30</citedRange></bibl>
                                calls it a passion prayer (<foreign xml:lang="de">Passionsgebet</foreign>) and notes that it is partially rhymed.
                                <bibl><ptr target="bm:Zettersteen1899Upsala"/><citedRange unit="page">510</citedRange></bibl>,
                                on the other hand, calls it a song of praise to God (<foreign xml:lang="de">Lobgesang auf Gott</foreign>).
                                <bibl><ptr target="bm:Loefgren1974Katalog"/><citedRange unit="page">30</citedRange></bibl> notes
                                that this text is written by the same hand as the <ref target="#ms_i2.20"/>.
                            </note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                                ኦእግዚኦ፡ ነአኵተከ፡ ወንሴብሐከ፡ ወንሰግድ፡ ለዕበየ፡ ሐይልከ፡ ወለጽንዓ፡ ፍቅርከ፡ እስመ፡ ፈኖከ፡ ለነ፡ ወልድከ፡ 
                                <sic resp="PRS6337Lofgren">ፍቁርከ፡</sic> ወኢምሕኮ፡ እምኔነ፡
                            </incipit>
                            <explicit xml:lang="gez">
                                ኢነጸረቶ፡ እሙ፡ በጊዜ፡ ሞቱ፡ ወኢኦድዎ፡ አዕርክቲሁ፡ ለሐውጾቱ። ጻመወ፡ በፈቃዱ፡ ባሕቲቱ፡ እስመ፡ መሐሪ፡ 
                                ውእቱ፡ ወመፍቀሬ፡ ሰብእ፡ ይብትክ፡ ወይፍታሕ፡ መአስረ፡ ኀጣውኢነ፡ ኀበ፡ ሀሎ፡ ነሀሉ፡ በከመ፡ ለሊሁ፡ አሰፈወነ፡ 
                                ሎቱ፡ ስብሐት፡ <add place="above">ዘ</add>እምኀቤነ፡ ወለነኒ፡ መንግሥቶ፡ ይክፍለነ፡ ይእዜኒ፡ ወዘልፈኒ፡ 
                                ወለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።
                            </explicit>
